                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Tri-Motors Safety Airways/20:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-11T10:00:00-04:30"
                            >May 11, 1929—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Local representative of New York, Rio, and Buenos Aires Line requests
                    following message be transmitted: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>For O’Neill, New York, Rio, and Buenos Aires Line, 929 Graybar Building,
                            New York City:</p>
                        <p>Have Boudouy cable France to have French interests instruct its
                            representatives here to assist my representations. At the present time
                            there is French mission here studying conditions and selling planes.
                            Thus far have made no representations whatever only sizing up situation.
                            Advise me what you do. This is important. Signed, Tennant.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
